==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sup
<hw>Sup</hw> <pr>(s⟦ucr⟧p)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Supped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Supping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>soupen</ets>
to drink, AS. <ets>s⟦umac⟧pan</ets>; akin to D. <ets>zuipen</ets>, G.
<ets>saufen</ets>, OHG. <ets>s⟦umac⟧fan</ets>, Icel.
<ets>s⟦umac⟧pa</ets>, Sw. <ets>supa</ets>, Dan. <ets>s⟦oum⟧be</ets>. Cf.
<er>Sip</er>, <er>Sop</er>, <er>Soup</er>, <er>Supper</er>.]</ety>
<def>To take into the mouth with the lips, as a liquid; to take or drink
by a little at a time; to sip.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There I'll <qex>sup</qex>⟦br⟧
Balm and nectar in my cup.</q> <rj><qau>Crashaw.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sup</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sup
<hw>Sup</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small mouthful, as of liquor or
broth; a little taken with the lips; a sip.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Tom Thumb had got a little <qex>sup</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Drayton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sup</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Sup
<hw>Sup</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Supper</er>.]</ety> <def>To
eat the evening meal; to take supper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I do entreat that we may <qex>sup</qex> together.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sup</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Sup
<hw>Sup</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To treat with supper.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Sup</qex> them well and look unto them all.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supawn</ent>⟦br⟧
